{"body": "I agree a simpler solution would be ideal. We've only seen this race a couple times on a pretty heavily-used JRuby/Rails app, so it's unlikely that lock contention, or dogpile effect, would see significant performance costs.\r\n\r\nTesting this would be difficult. We'd have to have some sort of fuzz-testing approach to see if we can hit the race condition right, and even then it wouldn't be deterministic. Thoughts?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2343081", "created_at": "2011-10-10T05:25:54Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/504#issuecomment-2343081", "updated_at": "2011-10-10T05:25:54Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 504, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/stephenjudkins", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b12ead92306a438050ef9001cf8247c0?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F419345a4c56c55ba30671ab8c25d2a73.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins/received_events", "gravatar_id": "b12ead92306a438050ef9001cf8247c0", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "stephenjudkins", "type": "User", "id": 8593, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/stephenjudkins/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52385f1fbd3543c151012181"}, "id": 2343081, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/504"}
